data.name: SheetFilterDescriptor
desc: represents a description of how a cell range is to be filtered.
The descriptor contains properties and a collection of filter conditions (filter fields) which control the behavior of a filter operation.

properties.name: ContainsHeader
desc: specifies if the first row (or column) contains headers which should not be filtered.

properties.name: CopyOutputData
desc: specifies if the filtered data should be copied to another position in the document.

properties.name: IsCaseSensitive
desc: specifies if the case of letters is important when comparing entries.

properties.name: MaxFieldCount
desc: returns the maximum number of filter fields in the descriptor.
This read-only property indicates the maximum count of fields the current implementation supports.

properties.name: Orientation
desc: specifies if columns or rows are filtered.

properties.name: OutputPosition
desc: specifies the position where filtered data are to be copied.
This is only used if SheetFilterDescriptor.CopyOutputData is TRUE.

properties.name: SaveOutputPosition
desc: specifies if the SheetFilterDescriptor.OutputPosition position is saved for future calls.
This is only used if SheetFilterDescriptor.CopyOutputData is TRUE.

properties.name: SkipDuplicates
desc: specifies if duplicate entries are left out of the result.

properties.name: UseRegularExpressions
desc: specifies if the TableFilterField.StringValue strings are interpreted as regular expressions.
